"Remember coming home after a day of school and pouring a big glass of chocolate milk - refreshing right?  This beer is like that.  A black/deep brown pour with a beautiful creamy head. I remember just how taken I was with the lacing the first time.  Each sip is measured for posterity along the glass down to the last gulp. Chocolate and something like a warm pumpernickel rye greet the nose.  The even smoothness of the creamy stout gives way to an initial subtle sweet latte flavor settling into a dark chocolate finish. I cannot remember which of my many preferred stouts was my favorite prior to my first LH-MS-N.  My next favorite will need to be pretty immaculate to force me away from this 'dairy queen.' I think you could drink this with a peanut butter and jelly, but on it's own this is a great after school/work snack!"
